{
  "stem": "19690.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And later, we found out that the SS had smashed the doors and took all the valuables out of the temple-- not the [? torahs, ?] but everything else-- and then pull-- pulled two wagons of hay into the synagogue and set them on fire with gasoline.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so that was that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Later that day, they came and arrested my father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they told us at the time that he would be in the local jail and that my mother should bring food to him-- the-- the meals.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So at noon or in the afternoon, she took a meal to him and then we were told we had to leave town immediately.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "At the time, my mother's younger sister who had married in 1932 and her husband were visiting, which no one knew.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He could drive.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My father was never a driver, but he wasn't available anyway.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "No one else knew how to drive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So the decision was made that he would drive us in one of the business cars, which we still owned, and take us to our-- my mother's oldest sister in Stuttgart.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So late at night-- the expression is 'en nacht und nabel,' in night and fog, we packed up what we could, my grandmother, my mother and I, and my aunt and uncle, and we drove to Stuttgart.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was a very foggy night and going along the Rhine River on the autostrasse-- it wasn't an autobahn yet at that time, it was very difficult.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But we got there early in the morning and the reception was less than cordial.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "She was worried about her husband who was also on a business trip.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He was also a salesman and he was caught in a small town and she didn't know whether he was OK or not.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
